{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":330914,"duration_api_ms":352345,"num_turns":29,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"024a20c6-4f8c-4c57-a444-87f8f080c6b1","total_cost_usd":1.3371406,"usage":{"input_tokens":21,"cache_creation_input_tokens":64126,"cache_read_input_tokens":931994,"output_tokens":13263,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":64126,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":21,"outputTokens":13263,"cacheReadInputTokens":931994,"cacheCreationInputTokens":64126,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.1984644999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":171,"outputTokens":6748,"cacheReadInputTokens":467526,"cacheCreationInputTokens":46410,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.13867610000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed the complete change set across all gn8 project rounds (7 commits). The implementation covers all four requirements from the project prompt: (1) increased retry limits (Transport 3→5, Schema 2→3, Timeout 2→3), (2) hard timeout enforcement via `tokio::time::timeout` in `spawn_and_wait` with child kill and artifact preservation, (3) differentiated `BinaryNotFound` (spawn-time `ErrorKind::NotFound`) from post-spawn exit codes (all → `TransportFailure`), and (4) exponential backoff (5s base, 60s cap) with cancellation-aware sleep in the engine retry loop. The service-level timeout in `service.rs` correctly adds a 30s buffer so the adapter's timeout fires first; both produce retryable `FailureClass::Timeout` errors. The cross-platform `force_kill` method is correct (SIGKILL on Unix, `TerminateProcess` via `Child::kill()` on Windows). Tests are comprehensive and pass. All existing engine tests were properly updated for new retry counts and `start_paused = true` to avoid real backoff delays. One minor gap: no test for the actual spawn-failure → `BinaryNotFound` code path.","amendments":[{"body":"Add a test in `tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs` that verifies when the backend binary truly does not exist (i.e., is not on PATH), `invoke()` returns `FailureClass::BinaryNotFound`. Currently the exit-code-127 test covers post-spawn classification, and retry_policy tests verify BinaryNotFound is terminal, but the actual spawn-failure → BinaryNotFound path in `process_backend.rs:986-987` (`ErrorKind::NotFound` branch) has no direct test. This is the critical non-retryable path that prevents wasting 5 retry attempts on a missing binary.","rationale":"The `BinaryNotFound` variant was newly added in this change set specifically to handle missing binaries as non-retryable failures. Without a test, a regression that removes the `ErrorKind::NotFound` check or misclassifies spawn failures would go undetected, potentially causing runs to retry 5 times against a binary that will never exist."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"81a6c185-2418-4c88-8667-4f3511064499"}
